      <p><xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eqn-4">Equation (4)</xref> shows that the function is the log odds ratio of a gene belonging to the gene set of interest, given the associated <italic>S</italic><sub><italic>mrna</italic></sub> value. Coefficient <italic>θ</italic><sub>1</sub> stands for the change in the log odds ratio of the gene belonging to the gene set of interest by a unit change in <italic>S</italic><sub><italic>mrna</italic></sub>.</p>
      <p>The model parameter is estimated based on the principle of maximum likelihood (<xref rid="ref-13" ref-type="bibr">Fu &amp; Li, 1993</xref>). Specifically, the following log likelihood function is maximized: <disp-formula id="NONUM-d2e941"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="peerj-06-4262-e005.jpg" mimetype="image" mime-subtype="png" position="float" orientation="portrait"/><tex-math id="M5">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
